## Parallel Execution Opportunities

**When**: Two tasks are independent and can run simultaneously

**Common Patterns**:

### Pattern 1: Main Task + Documentation
```
Main task completes (e.g., code written, tests pass)
  ├─> Continue with next user interaction
  └─> [PARALLEL] @keeper: "Update docs for completed task"
```

### Pattern 2: Independent Validations
```
Multiple test suites to run
  ├─> @validator instance 1: "Run unit tests"
  ├─> @validator instance 2: "Run integration tests"
  └─> @validator instance 3: "Run E2E tests"
```

### Pattern 3: Multi-Target Operations
```
Apply change to multiple modules
  ├─> @worker instance 1: "Update module A"
  ├─> @worker instance 2: "Update module B"
  └─> @worker instance 3: "Update module C"
```

**Example** (redshift-reporting):
```
After SQL conversion:
  ├─> User sees: "Conversion complete"
  ├─> [PARALLEL] @validator: "Run validation case"
  └─> [PARALLEL] @wiki-keeper: "Update wiki with conversion notes"

Saves: 30-45 seconds per workflow
```

